description: You'll love to entertain in this stunning duplex condominium. Constructed in 2015, this spacious (2018 SF) 3-bedroom, 2.5-bath has the feel of a single-family residence with a private entrance from the rear patio and parking area. The main level has an open floor plan including a chef's kitchen with white shaker cabinets, Thermador appliances & granite countertops, an island that seats 4, a separate dining area, and a large, sun-filled living room with a gas fireplace. Down the hall, there's a half bath and two king-size bedrooms with a Jack & Jill full bathroom in between. The primary bedroom suite is on the ground level, including a den/exercise room, a walk-in closet, and a dual shower/soaking tub en suite bathroom. No detail/amenity was spared: oak floors, crown moldings, Lutron lighting, HVAC (3 Nest thermostats), bathroom radiant flooring, a generous storage room, and a deeded parking space. Conveniently located within steps of the Broadway shops, the SB beaches, and the Seaport.
